function eliminateMaximum(dist, speed) {
    const n = dist.length;
    const timeToReachCity = dist.map((d, i) => Math.ceil(d / speed[i])).sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let eliminated = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < n && timeToReachCity[i] > i; i++) {
        eliminated++;
    }
    return eliminated;
}
```

    1. Calculate the time it takes for each monster to reach the city, and store these times in an array `time_to_reach_city`.
2. Sort the `time_to_reach_city` array in ascending order.
3. Iterate through the array and check if the time it takes for the monster to reach the city is greater than the current time (index `i`). If it is, eliminate the monster and increment the `eliminated` counter.
4. If the time it takes for any remaining monster to reach the city is less than or equal to the current time, break out of the loop.
5. Return the number of eliminated monsters.

